**who —** Wu Zetian — a FEMALE · generations sphere — one age, one woman

**what —** The only woman in Chinese history to rule as emperor in her own name — founder of her own Zhou dynasty, who reformed the civil service toward merit and expanded the empire.

**where —** 624–705 CE · China — the top woman of her age, restored to the record  Framework inputs: the generations of women; the record restored  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The only woman in Chinese history to rule as emperor in her own name — founder of her own Zhou dynasty, who reformed the civil service toward merit and expanded the empire.

**how —** Crystallized from the documented life and work of Wu Zetian.

**◌ the mythos —** The only woman in Chinese history to rule as emperor in her own name — founder of her own Zhou dynasty, who reformed the civil service toward merit and expanded the empire. the foremost woman of her generation, written back into the lineage

**the moniker —** ⟦Wu Zetian:WUZ:15c4c9⟧ · spoken *mux-ko-xes*

**the seal —** Vilified for centuries by historians who could not forgive a woman the throne — her competence buried under condemnation.

